00:14:34,673 --> 00:14:36,140
Hi, I'm here to see a patient.

235
00:14:36,242 --> 00:14:38,710
I'm sorry, visiting hours
don't start until noon.

236
00:14:38,777 --> 00:14:39,744
Noon?

237
00:14:39,845 --> 00:14:42,211
- Time of death?
- 10:00 a. m. on the dot.

238
00:14:43,182 --> 00:14:46,015
I can't wait until noon.
In fact, I can't wait much longer at all.

239
00:14:46,085 --> 00:14:47,245
I can't wait until noon.
In fact, I can't wait much longer at all.

240
00:14:47,653 --> 00:14:50,451
Jake's an old friend of mine from basic.
I heard he was here.

241
00:14:50,522 --> 00:14:53,082
I'm sorry, miss.
He'll still be here in two hours.

242
00:14:53,158 --> 00:14:56,821
- Please, you don't understand.
- I understand fine. We'll see you at noon.

243
00:15:08,507 --> 00:15:09,565
Jake.

244
00:15:10,109 --> 00:15:12,407
We just got your CAT scan back.

245
00:15:12,711 --> 00:15:13,769
And?

246
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:17,114
Why don't we talk for a moment?

247
00:15:56,522 --> 00:15:57,511
Jake.

248
00:15:58,190 --> 00:16:01,387
What are you doing out of bed?
And why are you wearing your uniform?

249
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:04,657
You know you're supposed
to be in your robe. Jake?

250
00:16:11,603 --> 00:16:13,230
Excuse me, Nurse?

251
00:16:15,107 --> 00:16:17,166
- Yes?
- The patient wants a second opinion.

252
00:16:17,276 --> 00:16:20,609
I've got a healthy male with a swollen leg.
lbuprofen and bed rest?

253
00:16:20,679 --> 00:16:22,613
No go. You know the rules.

254
00:16:22,681 --> 00:16:26,583
I've done that for four days.
I think I should see the doctor.

255
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:28,643
- Smoker?
- Once in a while.

256
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:31,684
He could have DVT.
You might wanna do an ultrasound.

257
00:16:31,757 --> 00:16:32,781
That's just me.

258
00:16:33,225 --> 00:16:35,250
I need to get out of here.

259
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:37,060
I'm sorry, Jake.

260
00:16:37,129 --> 00:16:40,121
Maybe you should stick around
a little longer.

261
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,397
What are you doing? Don't be stupid.

262
00:16:43,469 --> 00:16:45,460
No.
I told you, I gotta get out.

263
00:16:45,571 --> 00:16:47,266
I just talked to the doc and--

264
00:16:47,373 --> 00:16:49,841
Jake, put down the gun, please.

265
00:16:50,309 --> 00:16:51,674
Listen to her, Jake.

266
00:16:51,744 --> 00:16:55,475
I'll be back in a couple of hours.
Okay? You won't even miss me.

267
00:16:55,547 --> 00:16:56,878
No, don't.

268
00:16:58,017 --> 00:16:59,848
Jake, let her go.

269
00:16:59,918 --> 00:17:02,079
I told you, I just gotta get out of here.

270
00:17:02,187 --> 00:17:03,552
Don't move.

271
00:17:03,989 --> 00:17:05,650
Just take it easy.

272
00:17:13,565 --> 00:17:16,056
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to scare you.

273
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:18,465
Listen, tell them
I'll be back as soon as I can.

274
00:17:18,570 --> 00:17:20,868
Wait, where are you going, Jake?

275
00:17:24,977 --> 00:17:27,377
You okay, Nurse?
Yeah, I'm fine.

276
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:29,772
Stop!

277
00:17:30,616 --> 00:17:31,947
So is Jake.

278
00:17:32,584 --> 00:17:35,280
- I'm not sure I'd say that.
- Why?

279
00:17:35,521 --> 00:17:39,855
Because if we don't find him soon,
next time you see him, he'll be dead.

280
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:50,626
Jake was wounded overseas.

281
00:17:50,702 --> 00:17:55,162
The doctors removed the bullet and
sent him back to the States to recuperate.

282
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:58,334
Two weeks ago,
we learned that a bullet fragment...

283
00:17:58,444 --> 00:18:00,935
had become dislodged
and settled in his pulmonary artery.

284
00:18:01,013 --> 00:18:02,742
So you removed the fragment?

285
00:18:02,815 --> 00:18:05,648
We tried, but he began hemorrhaging
during surgery.

286
00:18:05,717 --> 00:18:07,378
When do you try again?

287
00:18:07,453 --> 00:18:10,149
Well, until this morning we had no plans.

288
00:18:10,222 --> 00:18:12,315
What happened this morning?

289
00:18:13,025 --> 00:18:15,892
A CAT scan revealed
that an embolism had formed.

290
00:18:15,961 --> 00:18:18,156
<i>We have no other choice</i>
<i>but to open him up again. </i>

291
00:18:18,230 --> 00:18:20,221
'Cause if the embolism
ruptures the artery....

292
00:18:20,299 --> 00:18:22,164
He'll die immediately.

293
00:18:23,368 --> 00:18:26,428
That kid has a time bomb ticking
inside of him.

294
00:18:26,905 --> 00:18:30,602
So let's just hope that
the MPs find him before it goes off.

295
00:18:33,745 --> 00:18:34,575
I don't get it.

296
00:18:34,646 --> 00:18:37,979
I save a guy only to learn
he could be dead by the end of the day.

297
00:18:38,050 --> 00:18:40,712
Once the symptoms set in,
shortness of breath, sweating...

298
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:41,946
it's only a matter of hours.

299
00:18:42,020 --> 00:18:44,284
Even if I find him
before the embolism kills him...

300
00:18:44,356 --> 00:18:46,085
there's no guarantee he'll survive.

301
00:18:46,158 --> 00:18:47,420
Okay, let's just think.

302
00:18:47,493 --> 00:18:50,553
You told me that Jake said
he had something to do.

303
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:52,859
Yeah. That's what I heard him
tell the MP.

304
00:18:52,931 --> 00:18:56,628
If you knew that you were gonna die
in a matter of hours, what would you do?

305
00:18:56,702 --> 00:18:59,728
I don't know. Cry. Get drunk.

306
00:19:00,539 --> 00:19:01,699
Say goodbye.

307
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:06,335
According to his enlistment papers,
Jake has no family, no next of kin.

308
00:19:09,014 --> 00:19:12,108
There was a photo in his wallet.
A picture of a girl.

309
00:19:12,184 --> 00:19:15,551
Her name is Bridget Elkins.
She couldn't be older than 19.

310
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:18,982
There's no Bridget.

311
00:19:19,057 --> 00:19:22,083
There is a George Elkins
at 567 Charleston Road.

312
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:24,527
- It could be her father.
- I'll take it. Thanks.

313
00:19:24,596 --> 00:19:26,894
By the way, you just missed your sister.

314
00:19:26,965 --> 00:19:28,762
- She came here?
- Yeah.

315
00:19:30,102 --> 00:19:33,367
You guys didn't happen to make plans
by any chance?

316
00:19:37,276 --> 00:19:39,676
I can take it. How bad did it go?

317
00:19:40,546 --> 00:19:43,481
She dumped you
for a bailiff on a motorcycle.

318
00:19:43,749 --> 00:19:48,379
Davis, look, she's my sister
and I love her, but she's complicated.

319
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:53,189
I should've known a girl like Meredith
would never go for a guy like me.

320
00:19:53,258 --> 00:19:56,159
- You really liked her, huh?
- Yeah.

321
00:19:56,995 --> 00:19:58,860
I may regret this, but take notes...

322
00:19:58,931 --> 00:20:01,900
'cause I'll tell you everything
you need to know about my sister.

323
00:20:04,436 --> 00:20:05,425
London, yes.

324
00:20:05,537 --> 00:20:08,062
But to be honest,
the city that I really love is Dublin.

325
00:20:08,173 --> 00:20:12,269
I lived there my junior year.
That's amazing. That's so cool.

326
00:20:12,377 --> 00:20:13,776
The next thing you know...

327
00:20:13,845 --> 00:20:16,336
you'll tell me you're thinking about
moving back there.

328
00:20:16,415 --> 00:20:18,440
Now this is getting weird.

329
00:20:23,956 --> 00:20:26,186
Someone you know?
No one important.

330
00:20:26,258 --> 00:20:29,455
Of course, I would be remiss
if I didn't mention my love for animals.

331
00:20:29,528 --> 00:20:33,794
I love all kinds.
Dogs, cats. I adore horses.

332
00:20:35,801 --> 00:20:36,961
I see.

333
00:20:37,869 --> 00:20:41,999
So Tru did a pretty good job, huh?
Telling you exactly what to say?

334
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:45,608
Let me tell you something
Tru doesn't know about me.

335
00:20:45,677 --> 00:20:48,271
I don't want a guy to be
just like me.

336
00:20:48,347 --> 00:20:52,078
I want a guy to be himself.
That's what really impresses me.

337
00:20:52,217 --> 00:20:53,844
- Be myself?
- Yeah.

338
00:20:54,553 --> 00:20:56,612
- Okay, I can do that.
- Good.

339
00:20:56,688 --> 00:20:57,848
So....

340
00:20:58,991 --> 00:21:01,050
You a <i>Lord of the Rings</i> fan?

341
00:21:09,234 --> 00:21:10,861
567 Charleston.

342
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:29,719
Jake.

343
00:21:31,823 --> 00:21:33,085
You okay?

344
00:21:34,226 --> 00:21:36,456
She's gone. They left.

345
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:44,796
You're that nurse from the hospital.

346
00:21:44,870 --> 00:21:46,667
It's okay, I'm alone.

347
00:21:47,873 --> 00:21:52,276
You have to go back.
Without that surgery, you'll die.

348
00:21:52,344 --> 00:21:55,780
And with it, I hear my chances
aren't that much better.

349
00:21:57,549 --> 00:22:00,575
Anyway, I'm not going back until I find her.

350
00:22:02,888 --> 00:22:04,116
Bridget?

351
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:07,420
I was 18.

352
00:22:08,226 --> 00:22:10,421
I was stationed at McAllister.

353
00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:13,195
She was finishing her senior year
in high school.

354
00:22:13,265 --> 00:22:15,290
You were in love with her.

355
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:18,903
Yeah. Crazy love.

356
00:22:20,906 --> 00:22:22,305
I saw her...

357
00:22:23,608 --> 00:22:26,668
and I just knew.

358
00:22:27,612 --> 00:22:29,910
Luckily, she felt the same way.

359
00:22:31,116 --> 00:22:32,708
That's what I thought.

360
00:22:33,385 --> 00:22:34,875
What happened?

361
00:22:36,088 --> 00:22:38,318
I don't know. That's just it.

362
00:22:39,691 --> 00:22:42,683
I had a 48- hour pass
before I was shipped out.

363
00:22:43,729 --> 00:22:46,289
The greatest two days of my life.

364
00:22:46,932 --> 00:22:48,695
Just me and Bridget.

365
00:22:50,268 --> 00:22:54,170
Then I deploy, and a telegram shows up.

366
00:22:54,239 --> 00:22:57,140
She said she never wanted
to see me again...

367
00:22:57,376 --> 00:22:59,344
that we were over. Done.

368
00:23:00,879 --> 00:23:03,643
I called, but her number was changed.

369
00:23:03,849 --> 00:23:06,647
I wrote, but the letters came back to me.

370
00:23:07,119 --> 00:23:11,283
And if you don't mind me asking,
what makes you want to see her now?

371
00:23:13,425 --> 00:23:15,416
As much as I'd like to...

372
00:23:16,061 --> 00:23:18,859
there are a lot of things I can't forget.

373
00:23:20,565 --> 00:23:21,896
About war...

374
00:23:23,402 --> 00:23:26,667
about seeing your best buddies shot down
in the desert...

375
00:23:26,772 --> 00:23:29,070
8, 000 miles from home.

376
00:23:30,909 --> 00:23:34,208
But the one thing I can't remember...

377
00:23:35,914 --> 00:23:38,747
is the one thing I swore I'd never forget.

378
00:23:40,085 --> 00:23:41,347
Her face.

379
00:23:46,057 --> 00:23:48,025
All I have left is this.

380
00:23:51,763 --> 00:23:53,253
I could die...

381
00:23:54,666 --> 00:23:56,759
on the table, or right now.

382
00:23:58,870 --> 00:24:01,304
- And if I do....
- You don't know that.

383
00:24:01,506 --> 00:24:02,973
And if I do...

384
00:24:04,810 --> 00:24:07,142
I don't want to close my eyes...

385
00:24:07,746 --> 00:24:10,078
and not be able to see her face.

386
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:21,983
Of course, now she's gone.

387
00:24:22,761 --> 00:24:24,729
Can't find her anywhere.

388
00:24:26,364 --> 00:24:28,559
There are a lot of ways
to find someone, Jake.

389
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:29,622
Really?

390
00:24:29,701 --> 00:24:33,762
If I help you, you promise me
you'll go back and get that surgery?

391
00:24:36,141 --> 00:24:37,199
Sure.

392
00:24:40,712 --> 00:24:43,647
Still, I don't know how I'm gonna find her.

393
00:24:43,748 --> 00:24:46,046
The house is empty. They moved.

394
00:24:47,118 --> 00:24:51,020
Look inside, all that's left
are light bulbs and old magazines.

395
00:24:51,823 --> 00:24:53,313
Old magazines?

396
00:24:54,226 --> 00:24:56,319
Hi, this is Bridget Elkins.

397
00:24:56,795 --> 00:24:59,958
How am I? To tell you the truth,
not too good.

398
00:25:00,432 --> 00:25:02,024
I've called three times this month...

399
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:06,400
and I still can't get you people
to send your magazine to my new address.

400
00:25:06,505 --> 00:25:07,563
Yeah.

401
00:25:08,073 --> 00:25:10,735
Just so it doesn't happen again,
could you do me a favor...

402
00:25:10,842 --> 00:25:14,403
and confirm that you have
the correct forwarding address?

403
00:25:15,814 --> 00:25:19,147
Yes? 4963 Denson.

404
00:25:19,217 --> 00:25:21,811
That's it. Thanks very much.

405
00:25:27,592 --> 00:25:31,289
You have no idea how many applicants
show up without a résumé.

406
00:25:31,363 --> 00:25:32,796
- No.
- Yes.

407
00:25:33,298 --> 00:25:36,267
I mean, just having one
puts you at the top of my list.

408
00:25:36,334 --> 00:25:40,134
Of course, I don't notice
any prior experience in real estate.

409
00:25:40,238 --> 00:25:42,399
That's because I don't have any.

410
00:25:42,507 --> 00:25:46,534
But look, I've been selling something
to someone since I was 16...

411
00:25:46,711 --> 00:25:50,704
and what I found is that
as long as you listen to the customer...

412
00:25:51,416 --> 00:25:53,782
you can be successful
no matter what your product is.

413
00:25:53,852 --> 00:25:56,377
All right then,
what are some of the unique qualities...

414
00:25:56,454 --> 00:25:58,581
that you could bring to this job?

415
00:25:58,657 --> 00:26:01,023
Laughs. A lot of laughs, Marjorie.

416
00:26:01,126 --> 00:26:05,460
But, seriously. Passion, sincerity...

417
00:26:06,398 --> 00:26:08,923
and a little thing I like to call"persistence."

418
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:11,161
Unique? Maybe not.

419
00:26:12,037 --> 00:26:15,473
But what this company needs? Absolutely.

420
00:26:19,978 --> 00:26:21,377
Here we are.

421
00:26:23,181 --> 00:26:26,617
Looks like Mr. Elkins
has been doing okay for himself.

422
00:26:29,588 --> 00:26:31,647
- How do I look?
- Great.

423
00:26:32,324 --> 00:26:33,348
Well.

424
00:26:33,425 --> 00:26:37,088
- Not bad for a dead man anyway.
- Come on, stop that.

425
00:26:38,630 --> 00:26:39,654
Hey.

426
00:26:39,731 --> 00:26:40,993
You're sweating.

427
00:26:41,066 --> 00:26:43,660
Once the symptoms set in,
shortness of breath, sweating...

428
00:26:43,735 --> 00:26:45,066
it's only a matter of hours.

429
00:26:48,340 --> 00:26:49,466
You stay here, I'll get her.

430
00:26:49,574 --> 00:26:52,839
You promise, as soon as you see her,
it's right back to the hospital.

431
00:26:52,911 --> 00:26:56,039
Yeah. Just one thing.

432
00:26:57,515 --> 00:27:00,882
If her father answers the door,
don't mention my name.

433
00:27:01,386 --> 00:27:04,287
- Why not?
- Bridget's a smart girl.

434
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:06,347
He's got big plans for her.

435
00:27:06,424 --> 00:27:09,689
Falling in love with a soldier was not one.

436
00:27:10,161 --> 00:27:12,152
Probably can't blame him.

437
00:27:12,364 --> 00:27:15,265
I mean, does your dad like the guys
you bring home?

438
00:27:15,333 --> 00:27:16,994
He never met them.

439
00:27:17,268 --> 00:27:20,260
I'm sorry. He's dead?

440
00:27:21,272 --> 00:27:22,796
Just by choice.

441
00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:42,589
- Hello.
- Hi. Is Bridget home?

442
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:46,119
- No, she's out right now.
- Could you tell me where I might find her?

443
00:27:46,197 --> 00:27:49,724
- I'm sorry, you are?
- A friend of hers from high school.

444
00:27:50,201 --> 00:27:52,761
You must not recognize me. Tru Davies.

445
00:27:52,871 --> 00:27:54,133
No, I can't say that I....

446
00:27:54,239 --> 00:27:56,730
New nose. And I lost, like, 20 pounds, too.

447
00:27:56,841 --> 00:27:58,934
Don't be embarrassed.
You wouldn't be the first.

448
00:27:59,044 --> 00:28:02,275
Tru. Yes, of course.
Why don't you come in for a moment?

449
00:28:05,950 --> 00:28:07,713
Now, what's so urgent?

450
00:28:07,952 --> 00:28:10,045
I'm only in town for a few hours.

451
00:28:10,121 --> 00:28:12,988
In fact, I'm on my way to the airport
and if I didn't see her--

452
00:28:13,058 --> 00:28:15,117
She's at school.
She's got class all afternoon.

453
00:28:15,193 --> 00:28:17,184
I'll tell her you stopped by, if you'd like.

454
00:28:17,262 --> 00:28:20,390
Or I could swing by campus,
if you point me in the right direction.

455
00:28:20,465 --> 00:28:23,332
Look, she'll back from the JC
in a few hours.

456
00:28:23,401 --> 00:28:25,835
Junior College,
but Bridget was a valedictorian.

457
00:28:25,937 --> 00:28:27,905
She could've written her own ticket.

458
00:28:40,652 --> 00:28:43,280
Come on, Jake. We're going back
to the hospital right now.

459
00:28:43,354 --> 00:28:44,343
Jake?

460
00:28:46,024 --> 00:28:47,286
Who are you?

461
00:28:47,358 --> 00:28:49,349
Did you bring Jake here?
Is that why you came?

462
00:28:49,427 --> 00:28:51,895
Yes, but you don't understand.
He needs to see Bridget.

463
00:28:51,963 --> 00:28:54,955
You leave my house.
And you stay away from my daughter.

464
00:28:55,033 --> 00:28:56,057
I said let go.

465
00:28:56,134 --> 00:28:58,568
You have to go with them.
I came to see Bridget.

466
00:28:58,636 --> 00:29:00,297
- I didn't see her.
- I know where she is.

467
00:29:00,405 --> 00:29:02,873
I promise you, Jake, I'll find her.
Just please go.

468
00:29:04,509 --> 00:29:07,239
Oh, my God. Hurry.

469
00:29:07,312 --> 00:29:09,177
- Get him back now.
- Come on, let's go.

470
00:29:09,247 --> 00:29:12,114
They're not too happy
about that jeep, by the way.

471
00:29:15,587 --> 00:29:16,986
I'll find her.

472
00:29:18,656 --> 00:29:21,216
You know, I don't even know your name.

473
00:29:22,026 --> 00:29:23,015
Tru.

474
00:29:23,628 --> 00:29:26,995
Tru. You're not really a nurse, are you?

475
00:29:27,866 --> 00:29:29,527
What makes you say that?

476
00:29:29,601 --> 00:29:32,468
You're some sort of angel.

477
00:30:08,339 --> 00:30:09,328
Can I help you?

478
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:12,637
I'm looking for Bridget Elkins.
The registrar said she was here.

479
00:30:12,710 --> 00:30:15,076
She was, yes.
But you just missed her.

480
00:30:15,146 --> 00:30:19,014
The class ended five minutes ago.
Do you know where she is now?

481
00:30:19,083 --> 00:30:20,550
Is Bridget in some sort of trouble?

482
00:30:20,618 --> 00:30:22,779
It's her grandmother. Nothing serious.

483
00:30:22,854 --> 00:30:26,017
She slipped in the tub again,
and Mr. Elkins asked me to find her.

484
00:30:26,090 --> 00:30:29,958
Let me see, if it helps you,
she normally meets Phillip after class.

485
00:30:30,361 --> 00:30:31,851
- Phillip?
- Yeah.

486
00:30:31,930 --> 00:30:33,989
They're quite
the popular couple on campus.

487
00:30:34,065 --> 00:30:37,057
Try the Metzler Building, 212.
He should be finishing up there.

488
00:30:37,135 --> 00:30:38,830
Thanks.

489
00:31:02,694 --> 00:31:05,219
Thanks, Regina. Say bye, Phillip.

490
00:31:05,496 --> 00:31:06,485
Bye.

491
00:31:08,333 --> 00:31:09,891
- Bridget?
- Yes?

492
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:13,504
- He's beautiful, your boy.
- Thank you.

493
00:31:15,406 --> 00:31:17,067
He looks just like his father.

494
00:31:19,911 --> 00:31:21,071
What?

495
00:31:21,179 --> 00:31:23,511
Listen, I'm a friend of Jake's.

496
00:31:23,615 --> 00:31:25,708
He needs to see you, both of you.

497
00:31:25,817 --> 00:31:26,943
What?

498
00:31:28,853 --> 00:31:30,946
I haven't heard from Jake
in a year- and- a- half--

499
00:31:31,022 --> 00:31:32,683
He may not survive the day.

500
00:31:40,965 --> 00:31:42,592
This is all a little bit much, okay?

501
00:31:42,667 --> 00:31:44,328
I haven't heard from Jake in 18 months.

502
00:31:44,402 --> 00:31:46,870
- Suddenly you show up--
- He doesn't know about Phillip.

503
00:31:46,938 --> 00:31:49,566
Why does that sound
like some sort of accusation?

504
00:31:50,008 --> 00:31:51,168
It's not.

505
00:31:54,345 --> 00:31:57,678
I found out I was pregnant
the day he was shipped out.

506
00:31:57,749 --> 00:31:59,979
And I tried to contact him,
but I couldn't.

507
00:32:00,218 --> 00:32:03,517
Obviously, he had no interest
in reaching me.

508
00:32:03,988 --> 00:32:07,446
You sent him a telegram.
You told him not to contact you.

509
00:32:07,625 --> 00:32:11,254
What? Telegram?
I don't know what he's told you, but....

510
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:17,599
I'm over him.
I don't know why I'm getting so upset.

511
00:32:17,669 --> 00:32:19,762
He wants to see you
before he goes into surgery.

512
00:32:19,837 --> 00:32:22,362
We could be at the hospital
in under an hour.

513
00:32:24,375 --> 00:32:26,809
Ten years ago, I lost someone that I love.

514
00:32:26,878 --> 00:32:30,575
And not a day goes by that I don't wish
I could see her one more time.

515
00:32:31,049 --> 00:32:33,677
You still have that chance, Bridget.

516
00:32:33,751 --> 00:32:36,720
Sorry. I can't.

517
00:32:39,157 --> 00:32:41,557
I lost him once, I can't lose him again.

518
00:32:59,444 --> 00:33:01,435
Guardian angel or stalker?

519
00:33:01,946 --> 00:33:03,379
You decide.

520
00:33:04,282 --> 00:33:06,011
I was in the neighborhood.

521
00:33:07,485 --> 00:33:09,282
How are you feeling?

522
00:33:09,354 --> 00:33:12,983
As soon as I'm stable,
they're taking me to surgery.

523
00:33:13,624 --> 00:33:16,320
After that, anyone's guess.

524
00:33:16,694 --> 00:33:18,855
- I'm so sorry, Jake.
- For what?

525
00:33:19,664 --> 00:33:21,359
I was supposed to help you.

526
00:33:21,432 --> 00:33:24,959
You wanted to see her,
and I couldn't do what you asked.

527
00:33:25,903 --> 00:33:27,427
Don't do that.

528
00:33:29,107 --> 00:33:31,507
- You tried.
- I failed.

529
00:33:31,976 --> 00:33:35,776
What? You didn't fail.
Why are you being so hard on yourself?

530
00:33:37,715 --> 00:33:39,649
I saw where she lives.

531
00:33:40,551 --> 00:33:42,382
I know she's in school.

532
00:33:43,054 --> 00:33:45,488
She sounds happy. Healthy.

533
00:33:45,990 --> 00:33:49,892
She was more alive for me today
than she has been in two years.

534
00:33:51,229 --> 00:33:53,527
That's nothing to apologize for.

535
00:34:04,509 --> 00:34:06,636
I thought he was never gonna go down.

536
00:34:07,912 --> 00:34:10,904
You hungry? There's--
No, thanks.

537
00:34:12,817 --> 00:34:16,446
A crazy thing happened today.
This woman came by...

538
00:34:17,055 --> 00:34:20,547
- said Jake wanted to see me.
- Really?

539
00:34:22,994 --> 00:34:26,657
She seems convinced that I sent him
some stupid breakup telegram.

540
00:34:27,031 --> 00:34:29,693
Listen, there's a lot of odd people
in the world.

541
00:34:29,767 --> 00:34:31,257
Nothing to take to heart.

542
00:34:35,773 --> 00:34:38,708
Please, tell me it wasn't you, Daddy.

543
00:34:39,710 --> 00:34:40,677
Sweetheart--

544
00:34:40,778 --> 00:34:42,746
Tell me that
you didn't sign my name.

545
00:34:42,814 --> 00:34:44,372
- That you didn't send it.
- Look at me.

546
00:34:44,482 --> 00:34:46,848
Not until you say
that you didn't send it.

547
00:34:48,786 --> 00:34:50,344
Because he's sick.

548
00:34:52,490 --> 00:34:53,855
He could die.

549
00:34:57,662 --> 00:34:59,926
You had your whole future ahead of you.

550
00:35:00,698 --> 00:35:03,394
Princeton, Stanford,
you could have gone anywhere.

551
00:35:04,936 --> 00:35:06,233
My God.

552
00:35:07,472 --> 00:35:09,667
- I knew it.
- You got knocked up by a soldier.

553
00:35:09,774 --> 00:35:11,969
You were the top of your class.
He was enlisted--

554
00:35:12,076 --> 00:35:13,703
- I loved him!
- Where did that get you?

555
00:35:13,811 --> 00:35:16,803
Running between daycare
and some third- rate community college.

556
00:35:17,381 --> 00:35:18,405
You could've been great.

557
00:35:18,516 --> 00:35:22,475
You are my father, you're supposed
to love me no matter what I am.

558
00:35:30,194 --> 00:35:34,494
You ever wonder how one little decision
can change your whole life?

559
00:35:35,466 --> 00:35:36,763
All the time.

560
00:35:36,834 --> 00:35:38,096
If I didn't join the Army....

561
00:35:38,169 --> 00:35:41,900
You never would've been stationed here.
You never would've met Bridget.

562
00:35:42,807 --> 00:35:45,037
Maybe I would have met her
somewhere else.

563
00:35:45,143 --> 00:35:48,203
I would've had a nine to five,
a house and kids.

564
00:35:51,816 --> 00:35:54,444
Man, we would have had some cute kids.

565
00:35:58,356 --> 00:36:00,085
Jake, listen....

566
00:36:07,365 --> 00:36:08,889
I'm sure you would have.

567
00:36:13,137 --> 00:36:14,570
Excuse me.

568
00:36:17,441 --> 00:36:18,999
Hello?
<i>Hey, hey. </i>

569
00:36:19,177 --> 00:36:22,010
Why don't you come meet me
so we can celebrate?

570
00:36:22,079 --> 00:36:23,341
<i>I can't make it tonight. </i>

571
00:36:23,414 --> 00:36:24,881
But congratulations, Harry.

572
00:36:24,949 --> 00:36:27,008
<i>Not sure how you knew, </i>
<i>but thanks to you...</i>

573
00:36:27,084 --> 00:36:29,211
she offered it to me on the spot.

574
00:36:29,287 --> 00:36:30,276
<i>That's great. </i>

575
00:36:30,354 --> 00:36:32,049
I'm so happy for you.

576
00:36:32,123 --> 00:36:34,921
And, thanks to me, I turned it down.

577
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:39,123
You know, screw the guy
if he can't love me for who I am.

578
00:36:39,263 --> 00:36:40,753
<i>I'II see you, okay? </i>

579
00:36:50,107 --> 00:36:52,871
- Bridget.
- Hi, Jake.

580
00:36:55,479 --> 00:36:56,741
You came.

581
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:01,117
God, look at you.

582
00:37:02,453 --> 00:37:05,513
You look beautiful.

583
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:15,528
Jake, there's someone I want you to meet.

584
00:37:16,601 --> 00:37:18,159
You have a son.

585
00:37:18,803 --> 00:37:21,931
We do. Phillip, say hi to your daddy.

586
00:37:25,042 --> 00:37:27,135
Hey.

587
00:37:41,259 --> 00:37:43,659
How did we screw things up so bad?

588
00:37:45,196 --> 00:37:47,721
- Don't talk.
- Were we too proud?

589
00:37:49,166 --> 00:37:50,531
Too stupid?

590
00:37:51,102 --> 00:37:52,501
Here we go, Corporal.

591
00:37:53,904 --> 00:37:55,929
All that matters is I'm here now.

592
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:59,932
So whatever happens to me,
I want you to have a good life.

593
00:38:00,044 --> 00:38:03,377
I want you to marry.
I want Phillip to have a father.

594
00:38:03,447 --> 00:38:04,812
He has a father.

595
00:38:05,783 --> 00:38:09,150
Have a good life, Bridge. Promise me.

596
00:38:09,487 --> 00:38:11,580
Jake, you're gonna be fine.

597
00:38:14,558 --> 00:38:16,253
Promise me, Bridge.

598
00:38:17,595 --> 00:38:19,187
Take care of him.

599
00:38:44,388 --> 00:38:46,151
It's taking so long.

600
00:39:01,972 --> 00:39:04,566
- It was a risk. We all knew that.
- What?

601
00:39:07,712 --> 00:39:09,737
Oh, my God.

602
00:39:16,821 --> 00:39:18,812
I am so sorry.

603
00:39:28,733 --> 00:39:30,098
I lost him.

604
00:39:30,167 --> 00:39:33,227
You didn't lose him, Tru.
His time was just up.

605
00:39:34,271 --> 00:39:36,136
Jake knew he wouldn't survive the surgery.

606
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:37,969
That's why he asked you for your help.

607
00:39:38,075 --> 00:39:40,509
But it's my job to prevent death.

608
00:39:40,911 --> 00:39:42,902
To save people. All that.

609
00:39:44,315 --> 00:39:46,909
Well, maybe Jake wasn't the one
who needed saving.

610
00:39:48,319 --> 00:39:50,844
Maybe you saved the person
you were supposed to.

611
00:39:51,555 --> 00:39:52,817
Bridget.

612
00:39:53,557 --> 00:39:56,890
You let her say goodbye,
because yesterday, she wasn't able to.

613
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:02,396
- This job's just confusing sometimes.
- I know.

614
00:40:03,934 --> 00:40:05,868
That's why you have me.

615
00:40:09,140 --> 00:40:11,301
<i>

616
00:40:16,547 --> 00:40:18,538
Key under the mat, right?

617
00:40:19,150 --> 00:40:22,415
You made it.
Yeah. Did you ever think I wouldn't?

618
00:40:24,021 --> 00:40:25,716
No. Never.

619
00:40:29,927 --> 00:40:32,657
- You okay?
- Better now.

620
00:40:33,864 --> 00:40:37,322
Why don't you relax?
There's just one thing I gotta do.

621
00:40:39,370 --> 00:40:41,736
<i>Leave a message</i>
<i>at the beep. </i>

622
00:40:41,806 --> 00:40:44,673
Hey, Dad. It's Tru.

623
00:40:45,943 --> 00:40:48,537
I know we haven't talked in a while...

624
00:40:50,214 --> 00:40:52,842
but I want you to know I'm doing okay.

625
00:40:53,617 --> 00:40:55,278
I have a new job.

626
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:58,948
I guess you could say I help people.

627
00:41:00,825 --> 00:41:03,794
Sometimes, if I'm lucky, they even help me.

628
00:41:05,496 --> 00:41:07,396
That's why I'm calling.

629
00:41:10,100 --> 00:41:14,002
Because I know how hard it is
for two people to find each other.

630
00:41:14,772 --> 00:41:18,173
Especially when one of them
doesn't want to be found.

631
00:41:20,010 --> 00:41:21,875
So, good night, Dad...

632
00:41:22,847 --> 00:41:26,806
I hope you're happy and well, because I am.

633
00:41:28,552 --> 00:41:32,454
And from now on,
you don't have to try to find me...

634
00:41:32,523 --> 00:41:34,252
because suddenly...

635
00:41:35,659 --> 00:41:37,320
I don't feel lost.

636
00:41:39,163 --> 00:41:41,654
<i>

637
00:41:50,274 --> 00:41:51,400
Sorry.

638
00:41:53,344 --> 00:41:54,709
Long day.

639
00:41:59,950 --> 00:42:01,508
Tell me about it.